    <item>
      <title>5 Million Miles - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/10/03/5-million-miles/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/10/03/5-million-miles/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 04 Oct 2025 02:38:42 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-9017" class="post-9017 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;5 Million Miles&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;After making some coconut milk on Tuesday, I hit a new milestone: 5 million Nook Miles! &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/10/03/5-million-miles/Array" alt="You got Nook Miles! (Balance: 5,000,040)" class="wp-image-9019" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I ran into Pascal while diving. He gave me a pearl in exchange for my scallop, but he also had some words of wisdom: He told me that if I need to say something hard, make sure it comes from a place of love&amp;#8230;or a place of pizza.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/10/03/5-million-miles/Array" alt="Pascal: If you gotta say something that's hard, be sure it comes from a place of love...or, at least, a place of pizza." class="wp-image-9020" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ve noticed that Pascal has several quotes that involve pizza. He&amp;#8217;s making me hungry, &lt;em&gt;maaan&lt;/em&gt;. 🍕 &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, I found a message bottle from Soleil on the beach. It contained a recipe for pull-apart bread. Several minutes later, June taught me the exact same recipe! &lt;em&gt;Dough&lt;/em&gt;-ja vu! What a coincidence!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I went to visit Bob, he asked if had a laser and a spaceship. He was making fun of my zap suit!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/10/03/5-million-miles/Array" alt="Bob: Are you on patrol? Do you have a laser? Do you have a spaceship? Can I get your autograph? A huh huh..." class="wp-image-9021" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He&amp;#8217;s supposed to be my friend! He&amp;#8217;s probably just jealous of me, Agent S, and Kid Cat. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Sunday, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;Imperial K.K.&amp;#8221; for me, Bob, and Agent S.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;C.J. was in town on Tuesday, and I sold him 16 fish for 155,475 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Today, I returned a lost bag to Merengue. She rewarded me with a pullover jacket.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Flick was in town, and I sold him 18 bugs for 101,250 bells.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today I posted my (almost) monthly train animation showing my villager arrivals and departures for the month. Check it out!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-9-16 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing - My September 2025 Arrivals and Departures #animalcrossing #shorts" width="557" height="990" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VCrBHEr_4xk?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/10/03/5-million-miles/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-10-03T22:38:42-04:00"&gt;October 3, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/5m-miles-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Summoning Mira - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Oct 2025 03:15:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18386" class="post-18386 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Summoning Mira&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, I did something I probably haven&amp;#8217;t done in years: I popped a balloon with my net.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Jeff pops a balloon present with a net, as Jeremiah watches." class="wp-image-18387" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, it only had a balloon floor inside. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over by the statue fountain, I found a lost item (a bag) on the ground.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="I picked up a lost item!" class="wp-image-18388" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I briefly got excited when Cube told me it belonged to him&amp;#8230;but he only rewarded me with a royal shirt. Not his photo. What a royal pain. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, I visited Molly and she asked me to bring Mira over to her house. As soon as I walked outside, I found Mira right there! I love easy requests. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Mira: What?! I'm being summoned?!" class="wp-image-18389" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;So we made the long, three-foot trek to Molly&amp;#8217;s house and went inside.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Mira walks inside of Molly's door." class="wp-image-18390" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Once inside, Mira asked Molly what was so important that she had to drag her &amp;#8220;all the way&amp;#8221; over to her house. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Mira: What d'ya need, Molly? It had better be important to drag me all the way over here." class="wp-image-18391" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Molly just wanted to return Mira&amp;#8217;s pineapple bed that she borrowed. Who borrows a &lt;em&gt;bed&lt;/em&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Molly: I just wanted to return your pineapple bed to you in case you needed it for something." class="wp-image-18392" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;For sleeping. The &amp;#8220;something&amp;#8221; is sleeping.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mira took the item back, and she quickly went on her way.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Mira's ears are visible as Mira leaves Molly's house." class="wp-image-18393" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Anyway, Molly rewarded me with a weight bench for helping her out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jeremiah said there was a rumor going around that he had a world-famous mixing bowl collection. I guess his supposed collection is &lt;em&gt;bowling &lt;/em&gt;everyone over. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Jeremiah: But now there's a rumor going around that I have a world-famous mixing bowl collection!" class="wp-image-18394" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Lolly asked me for some furniture, and I gave her a tall oombloid. She seemed to like it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Lolly: A tall oombloid! Oh my!" class="wp-image-18396" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In return, she gave me a bunk bed. What&amp;#8217;s with everyone passing around beds today?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Gulliver was down on the beach, and he was talking about curry and the Taj Mahal.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Gulliver: I want to go there just to try all the food they have to offer! Yum curry! Yum naan! Yum veggie korma!" class="wp-image-18397" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I knew he was headed to India, so he will send me a gift from there next time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After selling my fossils and unwanted gifts, I returned home. But Rolf barged in to visit with me. He asked me an odd question&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/Array" alt="Rolf: Do you use one of those things? Those vroom-vroom thingies? Those scare the heck out of me!" class="wp-image-18398" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;A vacuum? Maybe I should use one to keep visitors away. 😛&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a typewriter before making his escape. See you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/09/30/summoning-mira/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-30T23:15:58-04:00"&gt;September 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-30T23:15:59-04:00"&gt;September 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/20250928_HNI_0032.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Sports in her DNA - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 28 Sep 2025 03:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13636" class="post-13636 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Sports in her DNA&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I found a new house and a new villager in town. Nana&amp;#8217;s replacement is Deena the duck.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="Deena: I just moved into town, and I really haven't had time to get settled yet. My name is Deena." class="wp-image-13637" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ve had her before (back in 2012), and more recently in Wild World (in 2022). She&amp;#8217;s not particularly one of my favorites, but I don&amp;#8217;t hate her either. But she is a downgrade from Nana, in my opinion.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I saw a shark fin in the ocean, or at least I thought I did. Instead, it was an ocean sunfish&amp;#8230;but that&amp;#8217;s not a bad catch either! Monty enjoyed watching me reel it in.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="I caught an ocean sunfish! I'm feeling pretty sunny now!" class="wp-image-13638" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Pascal was in town, but I again couldn&amp;#8217;t find any scallops to give him. Still, he told me that some people just help out to feel good about themselves.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="Pascal: Some people want to help you just to feel good about themselves. But the help is still nice, maaan." class="wp-image-13639" style="width:500px;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Sure, the help is nice, but be careful not to rely on the people who only pretend to care.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At the Roost, Antonio told me he was trying to cut back on his coffee chugging. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="Antonio: I promised myself yesterday to cut back on the coffee chugging. Only up to 7 a day!" class="wp-image-13640" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I think he means *down* to 7 a day.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But he said he can&amp;#8217;t resist Brewster&amp;#8217;s intense lattes.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="Antonio: But the lattes Brewster makes are INTENSE! I can't stop downin' them, up my nose! WOOO!" class="wp-image-13641" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rosie has been sick with a cold, so I gave her some medicine yesterday and again today. Get well soon, Rosie!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="Rosie: Thanks, la-di-da. Maybe the sleep ghosts will leave me alone now." class="wp-image-13642" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tonight, I got to see inside of Deena&amp;#8217;s house now that she&amp;#8217;s all unpacked. Even though she has a normal personality, her house looks a jock&amp;#8217;s house (or a gym) with all the sports equipment and lockers.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="The inside of Deena's house." class="wp-image-13643" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Maybe sports is just in her D(ee)-N-A.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I went over to the Roost to check out K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show. I asked him for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Tango&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Tango." class="wp-image-13644" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On my way back home from the Roost, I found a scallop on the beach. I put it in a letter so that I&amp;#8217;ll have it for the next time Pascal shows up.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I found two items in the recycle bin today, an office locker and a high-end stereo. I&amp;#8217;m surprised Deena didn&amp;#8217;t snag that office locker for her gym. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I recently posted my latest City Folk Moments video, so I hope you&amp;#8217;ll check it out!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="ACCF - City Folk Moments #29 (Animal Crossing)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ygYoZvTVmAY?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/09/27/sports-in-her-dna/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-27T23:59:00-04:00"&gt;September 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-28T11:17:24-04:00"&gt;September 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/RUU_8359-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Avengers - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 28 Sep 2025 02:29:22 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-9005" class="post-9005 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;The Avengers&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Monday (September 22nd) was Ankha&amp;#8217;s birthday, and I headed over to her house for her party. I gave her a hyacinth lamp that I crafted for her. She loved it!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Ankha: Are you serious? You're GIVING me a hyacinth lamp?" class="wp-image-9006" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Forest&amp;#8217;s newest resident Kid Cat was also at the party.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Kid Cat: Today is Ankha's big day, psst. Everyone's in party-flex mode!" class="wp-image-9007" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Julian the unicorn was camping at the campsite for the third time. Even though I like him, I did not ask him to move in. But I did play a game with him, and I won a free rattan table lamp.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Julian, at the campsite: It's a diamond...and that's red!" class="wp-image-9008" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The next day, I had a chat with Louie and he looked up at an odd angle. He was looking up at his double-sided wall clock, but it looked weird.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Louie: What? Are you checking out my double-sided wall clock?" class="wp-image-9009" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I saw my two superheroes stretching outside of Resident Services. I joined in, and Peanut did as well. Watch out for us, we&amp;#8217;re the Avengers. 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Agent S, Kid Cat, Jeff, and Peanut stretching outside of town hall." class="wp-image-9010" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, the final Bug-Off of the year was held. Static told me he was going to go all-out to win, but he&amp;#8217;ll try to leave a few (small) bugs for me. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Static: Enjoyin' the Bug-Off? I'm goin' all out this time. I'll try to leave a few for you, in my tail. Small ones." class="wp-image-9011" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Bones was taking a more laid-back approach. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Bones: I'm not too worried about how I do in the Bug-Off. I'll just wander around with a net catching everything I can!" class="wp-image-9012" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I played one round of the competition, and I caught 12 bugs. That was good for 14 points.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Catching a tiger butterfly as the Bug-Off time expires." class="wp-image-9013" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I sold the 12 bugs for 4,260 bells, and then I redeemed 10 points for a spider doorplate. Since it&amp;#8217;s almost October, I put that on my door. I moved my lucky horseshoe door decoration to inside my house.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After I sold my fossils and some other stuff, I had enough money to kick my savings balance up to a new milestone: 125 million bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/Array" alt="Savings Balance: 125,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-9014" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Tuesday, I sold 18 bugs to Flick for 96,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Wednesday, I sold 17 fish to C.J. for 181,350 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gullivarrr on Thursday, and he sent me another pirate bandanna.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/09/27/the-avengers/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-09-27T22:29:22-04:00"&gt;September 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ankha-bday2025-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Another Jock Frog - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 27 Sep 2025 02:50:03 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8391" class="post-8391 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Another Jock Frog&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Filbert told me that he is now over his cold. He thanked me for the medicine I gave him last week, and he gave me some diner tile (flooring). He felt the need to remind me that the medicine was vile, though. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/Array" alt="Filbert: Uh huh huh huh! That medicine you gave me was vile, dude." class="wp-image-8392" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, it was Truffles that was sick with a cold! So I gave her some medicine too. These colds can be annoying in the older games, when the sickness just moves from one animal to another.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I noticed a new house, and I went inside to meet my newest neighbor: Frobert!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/Array" alt="Frobert: Hey, nice to meetcha! I'm Frobert! You're Jeff, right?" class="wp-image-8393" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He&amp;#8217;s pretty cool! And I thought it was interesting that Drift was replaced with Frobert. I traded one jock frog for another!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Another surprising thing was that he was already unpacked. So that means he actually moved in yesterday, but I didn&amp;#8217;t notice! I apparently walked right by his house without realizing it belonged to a new villager. Oops. I wish villagers&amp;#8217; house lights were always on when a villager is home, like they are in City Folk. In Wild World, the lights are off in the daytime, so it&amp;#8217;s easy to miss someone.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I spotted Wendell in town, so I went back to my house to grab the gar I had saved for him. I took it over to him, and he gobbled it down. He loved it!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/Array" alt="Wendell: Ahhhhhhhh! Mmm...burp! So very delicious! So very full and happy!" class="wp-image-8394" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As expected, he gave me the &amp;#8220;overhead view D&amp;#8221; pattern. It&amp;#8217;s part of the Nazca lines, and I now have three of the four pieces to it. I had to replace one of my road patterns, but that&amp;#8217;s alright. I wasn&amp;#8217;t planning on using them anytime soon anyway.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/Array" alt="Three of the four overhead view patterns from Wendell." class="wp-image-8395" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, I&amp;#8217;ll have to wait (at least) until next summer to complete the Nazca lines set. That&amp;#8217;s because I need a giant snakehead for the last piece, and those are out of season until next June.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Speaking of fishing, I caught a few big (or valuable) fish in the rain tonight&amp;#8230;but not a coelacanth, sadly. However, I reeled in a red snapper, a king salmon, and a blue marlin.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/26/another-jock-frog/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-26T22:50:03-04:00"&gt;September 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-26T22:53:31-04:00"&gt;September 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/filbert-vile.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Drifting Away - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 03:11:04 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8380" class="post-8380 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Drifting Away&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Today, I found a goodbye letter from Drift in the mail. He has hopped out of town without warning. Was he upset that I didn&amp;#8217;t use his song as the town tune last week?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array" alt="Hoo-ha, Jeff, I'm moving. I have my reasons. No worries, yo! I'm sure you'll remember me fondly. Keep pumpin'! See ya! -From Drift" class="wp-image-8381" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I spoke with Pippy, she referenced the fact that two people live in my house. Villager is the other person, and I only created him to unlock spotlight items at Nook&amp;#8217;s shop.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array" alt="Pippy: Whaaaaaaaaaat?! There's only two of you in that house?!" class="wp-image-8383" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then went on to assume that Villager is cute?&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array" alt="Pippy: I'm guessing from your smile that the person you're roomin' with is cute!" class="wp-image-8382" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She wanted me to introduce them, but that&amp;#8217;s probably not going to happen.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over by the museum, Truffles mentioned that Blathers wanted to be a pro archaeologist.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array" alt="Truffles: Well, I heard that he once wanted to be a pro archaeologist!" class="wp-image-8384" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then said it seems like everyone has skeletons in the closet. And that made me wonder what was so wrong about wanting to be an archaeologist? But then, it hit me. Maybe she was making a pun. After all, it&amp;#8217;s reasonable to think an aspiring archaeologist might literally have skeletons in their closet. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array" alt="Truffles: ...Boy, seems like EVERYONE around here has skeletons in the closet, snoutie!" class="wp-image-8385" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Filbert was sick with a cold today, so I gave him some medicine. Get well soon!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Later, I headed over to the Roost. K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;Imperial K.K.&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: Imperial K.K.!" class="wp-image-8387" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Before wrapping up my game for the night, I decided to make a few laps around the &amp;#8220;lake,&amp;#8221; to look for a gar. On about my 5th trip around, I caught one!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array" alt="I caught a gar! ...Nose like a GARden hose!" class="wp-image-8388" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll be saving this one for Wendell, so I put it in my house for now. Hopefully I&amp;#8217;ll remember it the next time Wendell shows up.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/09/20/drifting-away/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-09-20T23:11:04-04:00"&gt;September 20, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/drift-out.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
